    			</language>
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Sic transit gloria mundi.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Ridiculous. So passes the glory of the world.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Prudentia, theoria: fortitudo, Praxis.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Prudence in theory; strength in Action.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Fortuna, fortitudo vna.
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Fortune, one strength.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
    		
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Animus est, qui facit foelicem, aut miserum.
    					</marginalia_text>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				The mind is that which creates happiness or misery.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
        
    		<marginalia hand="Italian">
    			<language ident="LA">
    				<position book_orientation="270" place="right_margin">
    					<marginalia_text>
    						Vilis animus est, qui non dominatur corpori. Magnus animus, ideóq[ue]	
    						tranquillus, tam Corpori imperat, quàm fortuna[e]; quantumcunq[ue] aut
    						illud a[e]gru[m] aut ha[e]c afflict[a].
    					</marginalia_text>
    					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
    				</position>
    			</language>
    			<translation>
    				Of little value is the mind which does not control the body. A great and tranquil mind, therefore, 
    				both rules the Body, and fortune: however infirm the former or oppressive the latter.
    			</translation>
    		</marginalia>
        
